<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-03-14T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-03-14T06:00:00-05:00" n="722" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d722">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.632/98: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stockton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-14T12:00:00+01:00">March 14,
                                1931—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received March 14—10:35
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>13. National Council approved supplemental [article] and Senate
                            reservation yesterday. They will go to Federal Council Tuesday.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stockton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>